dct_title_s: Map of the Fly River drawn from the original charts made by Signor L. M. D'Albertis by W. J. Turner
dct_description_sm: Includes notes describing banks, villages, and vegetation along waterways. Delta and islands of river are shown. Conjectural coastlines shown by dotted lines. Includes inset map of New Guinea, surrounding islands, and portions of northern Australia [scale ca. 1:11,930,000]. Position of Fly River and its delta on island is shown. Relief shown by hachures. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 1 (1879), no. 1, pp. 4-16; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
